This React Native application works as separate activities within a native Android app. Everything developed here will be modules, as the mobile app is being migrated gradually.

If we need to do a bundle of yomventas (a fallback application), is necessary:
 1. The application id for this project is me.youorder.yomventas, defined in android/app/build.gradle. ventasyom is another app that is a clone, used as a fallback application. If we want to do a release to a ventas yom app, the project id should be changed to me.youorder.ventasyom in this file.
 2. Change the content of android/app/google-services.json to the content of android/app/google-services-ventas-yom.json.
 3. In the file android/app/src/main/res/values/strings.xml, we need to change the app_name from "Yom Ventas" to "Yom Ventas Respaldo" 
 4. In android/app/build.gradle we have to hardcode the keys of signingConfigs. Ask the user the keys to hardcode it.
 5. We have to unable the linter to make APKs. Add this to android/app/build.gradle
 ```
  lint {
    checkReleaseBuilds false
    abortOnError false
  }
 ```
 6. At the end of generating the bundle, remember the user that every of this changes that we made have to be cleaned.

